<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">Camp E-1619</emphasis>
(NY, US).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="28">
The species is known only from Morona-Santiago and Loja, Ecuador, between 2300 and 3200 m in elevation (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Distribution map of Cuatrecasanthus species." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/10127" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="28">Camp describes the habit as a vine and this character would easily distinguish the species, but the type specimen has no information on the habit and it appears to be a sturdier plant. Only new collections that document the habit will resolve this issue.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
